Week of March 24 [...] BPA competes at National Leadership Conference in Orlando

Congratulations to the 46 students who advanced to the Business Professionals of America National Leadership Conference Championship. They competed in over 15 categories against other students from across the nation and China. Many placed in the top 10 of their specialty area and several placed in the top 3. Between presentations, they enjoyed Disney Springs and Magic Kingdom.

##### BPA NLC Results

Etheredge receives NJHS Outstanding Achievement Award

Congratulations to Elise Etheredge for receiving the National Junior Honor Society Outstanding Award.

This award honors students who rock it in all five NJHS pillars: scholarship, service, leadership, character and citizenship.

Citation2021), [...] Students’ perceptions, knowledge and attitudes about SET were identified as factors influencing students’ decisions to participate in SET processes. Students commented that their lack of knowledge about the SET process and how they were used to improve teaching performance and course content was a barrier to completing the SET surveys (Cone et al. Citation2018; Hoel and Dahl Citation2019; Gupta et al. Citation2020; Stein et al. Citation2021).
